    <p class="text-gray-300">These represent 3-round differentials of probability 2&lt;sup&gt;−&lt;/sup&gt;11.&lt;sup&gt;19&lt;/sup&gt;, where we do not care about the intermediate differences, i.e. the type-2 characteristics considered as differentials. When putting two such differentials together, we get a 6-round differential of probability at least 2&lt;sup&gt;−&lt;/sup&gt;2·11.&lt;sup&gt;19&lt;/sup&gt; = 2&lt;sup&gt;−&lt;/sup&gt;22.&lt;sup&gt;38&lt;/sup&gt; , which is similar to the type-1 characteristic considered as a differential, except that after 3 rounds we know the difference is (a k 0).</p>

