    <p class="text-gray-300">Note, that the first observation above can be used in the beginning of the 6-round iterated differential described in Section 3 or the impossible differentials described in Section 4, as it yields an output difference of the form (α k 0), which is exactly the starting point needed.</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300">However, compared to the generic extension by two rounds on top, described in Section 3.4, this approach is impaired in two ways:</p>

